[],\"refs\":[],\"alt\":\"<entity_name>\",\"prompt_text\":\"<entity_name>\",\"type\":\"entity\",\"name\":\"<entity_name>\",\"category\":\"<entity_category>\",\"priority\":1,\"metadata\":null,\"entity_data\":null,\"extra_params\":{\"disambiguation\":\"<city, state/province, country | address>\"},\"status\":\"done\",\"notes\":null,\"entity_index\":null},{\"matched_text\":\"entity[\\\"<ref_id>\\\", \\\"<entity_name>\\\"]\",\"prefix\":null,\"start_idx\":3305,\"end_idx\":3343,\"safe_urls\":[],\"refs\":[],\"alt\":\"<entity_name>\",\"prompt_text\":\"<entity_name>\",\"type\":\"entity\",\"name\":\"<entity_name>\",\"category\":\"<ref_id>\",\"priority\":1,\"metadata\":null,\"entity_data\":null,\"extra_params\":null,\"status\":\"done\",\"notes\":null,\"entity_index\":null}],\"resolved_model_slug\":\"gpt-5-3\",\"request_id\":\"3076b6d1-a9e8-4931-b930-412548c574f1\",\"message_type\":\"next\",\"turn_exchange_id\":\"6f3d7f13-0d85-439d-81b7-5bca61a0dc80\",\"model_slug\":\"gpt-5-3\",\"default_model_slug\":\"gpt-5-3\",\"parent_id\":\"e5ef226d-1f3a-48e1-a827-329bad6e2734\",\"is_visually_hidden_from_conversation\":true,\"can_save\":false},\"recipient\":\"assistant\",\"channel\":null},\"parent\":\"e5ef226d-1f3a-48e1-a827-329bad6e2734\",\"children\":[\"abaa3986-c918-4229-b740-dfa9f4bf230d\"]},\"abaa3986-c918-4229-b740-dfa9f4bf230d\":{\"id\":\"abaa3986-c918-4229-b740-dfa9f4bf230d\",\"message\":{\"id\":\"abaa3986-c918-4229-b740-dfa9f4bf230d\",\"author\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"name\":null,\"metadata\":{}},\"create_time\":1774244784.2842216,\"update_time\":null,\"content\":{\"content_type\":\"code\",\"language\":\"unknown\",\"response_format_name\":null,\"text\":\"search(\\\"what would you recommend for low light?\\\")\"},\"status\":\"finished_successfully\",\"end_turn\":null,\"weight\":1.0,\"metadata\":{\"citations\":[],\"content_references\":[],\"resolved_model_slug\":\"gpt-5-3\",\"request_id\":\"3076b6d1-a9e8-4931-b930-412548c574f1\",\"message_type\":\"next\",\"turn_exchange_id\":\"6f3d7f13-0d85-439d-81b7-5bca61a0dc80\",\"model_slug\":\"gpt-5-3\",\"default_model_slug\":\"gpt-5-3\",\"parent_id\":\"2a6a0d2b-914f-43a1-a04f-2224429b25e7\",\"model_switcher_deny\":[],\"can_save\":false},\"recipient\":\"web\",\"channel\":null},\"parent\":\"2a6a0d2b-914f-43a1-a04f-2224429b25e7\",\"children\":[\"24336aaa-eff6-44de-a9ed-b4d579bca6f9\"]},\"24336aaa-eff6-44de-a9ed-b4d579bca6f9\":{\"id\":\"24336aaa-eff6-44de-a9ed-b4d579bca6f9\",\"message\":{\"id\":\"24336aaa-eff6-44de-a9ed-b4d579bca6f9\",\"author\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"name\":null,\"metadata\":{\"real_author\":\"tool:web\"}},\"create_time\":1774244786.381122,\"update_time\":null,\"content\":{\"content_type\":\"text\",\"parts\":[\"If your apartment is **truly low light (no direct sun, maybe a dim window)**, you want plants that don’t just *tolerate* it—they’re **adapted to it**.\\n\\nHere are the **best, no-nonsense picks** ranked by reliability:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🥇 Best overall (almost impossible to kill)\\n\\nimage_group{\\\"aspect_ratio\\\":\\\"1:1\\\",\\\"query\\\":[\\\"ZZ plant indoor dark room\\\",\\\"Zamioculcas zamiifolia modern apartment\\\",\\\"raven zz plant black leaves\\\",\\\"zz plant low light corner\\\"],\\\"num_per_query\\\":1}\\n\\n### ZZ Plant (*Zamioculcas zamiifolia*)\\n- Handles **very low light better than almost anything**\\n- Needs water only every few weeks\\n- Thick stems store water → hard to kill  \\n- Even survives far from windows citeturn0search1turn0search0  \\n\\n👉 If you want one plant that *just works*, this is it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🥈 Best “clean aesthetic” plant\\n\\nimage_group{\\\"aspect_ratio\\\":\\\"1:1\\\",\\\"query\\\":[\\\"snake plant indoor corner low light\\\",\\\"sansevieria modern decor\\\",\\\"tall snake plant minimal apartment\\\",\\\"snake plant bedroom low light\\\"],\\\"num_per_query\\\":1}\\n\\n### Snake Plant (*Dracaena trifasciata*)\\n- Thrives in **low light + neglect**\\n- Water every few weeks\\n- Tall, structured look (closest vibe to a cactus)  \\n- Very beginner-friendly citeturn0search1turn0search7  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🥉 Best for darker corners (true shade plant)\\n\\nimage_group{\\\"aspect_ratio\\\":\\\"1:1\\\",\\\"query\\\":[\\\"cast iron plant aspidistra indoor low light\\\",\\\"aspidistra dark room plant\\\",\\\"cast iron plant victorian houseplant\\\",\\\"aspidistra elatior indoor\\\"],\\\"num_per_query\\\":1}\\n\\n### Cast Iron Plant (*Aspidistra elatior*)\\n- Literally named for being **hard to kill**\\n- Can survive in **very dim rooms**\\n- Slow-growing but extremely durable citeturn0search1  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🌿 Best trailing / shelf plant\\n\\nimage_group{\\\"aspect_ratio\\\":\\\"1:1\\\",\\\"query\\\":[\\\"pothos plant low light shelf\\\",\\\"jade pothos indoor trailing\\\",\\\"pothos hanging apartment low light\\\",\\\"epipremnum aureum low light\\\"],\\\"num_per_query\\\":1}\\n\\n### Pothos (especially “jade” pothos)\\n- Grows well in **low light corners**\\n- Trails nicely from shelves\\n- Very forgiving with watering citeturn0search1  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🌸 If you want something softer / more decorative\\n\\nimage_group{\\\"aspect_ratio\\\":\\\"1:1\\\",\\\"query\\\":[\\\"peace lily indoor low light bloom\\\",\\\"birds nest fern indoor low light\\\",\\\"fern bathroom low light humidity\\\",\\\"peace lily apartment decor\\\"],\\\"num_per_query\\\":1}\\n\\n### Peace Lily or Bird’s Nest Fern\\n- Do well in low light\\n- More “lush” look vs. structural\\n- Need a bit more consistent watering  \\n- Some even flower (peace lily) citeturn0search4  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## ⚙️ What I’d actually recommend for *you*\\n\\nGiven you said **apartment + low light**, I’d go:\\n\\n- **1st choice:** ZZ plant  \\n- **2nd choice:** Snake plant (if you want that cactus vibe)  \\n- **Add-on:** Pothos if you want something hanging  \\n\\nThat combo covers:\\n- floor plant  \\n- vertical structure  \\n- trailing greenery  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Quick reality check (important)\\n\\n- “Low light” ≠ no light  \\n- Plants will **grow slower** and need **less water**  \\n- If it’s *really* dark (like no window), consider a $15 grow light  \\n\\n---\\n\\nIf you want, tell me how far your nearest window is (like “10 ft away, north-facing”), and I’ll dial this into **specific placements + exact species** for your layout.\"]},\"status\":\"finished_successfully\",\"end_turn\":true,\"weight\":1.0,\"metadata\":{\"finish_details\":{\"type\":\"stop\",\"stop_tokens\":[200002]},\"is_complete\":true,\"content_references\":[{\"matched_text\":\"image_group{\\\"aspect_ratio\\\":\\\"1:1\\\",\\\"query\\\":[\\\"ZZ plant indoor dark room\\\",\\\"Zamioculcas zamiifolia modern apartment\\\",\\\"raven zz plant black leaves\\\",\\\"zz plant low light corner\\\"],\\\"num_per_query\\\":1}\",\"prefix\":null,\"start_idx\":269,\"end_idx\":461,\"safe_urls\":[\"https://images.openai.com/static-rsc-3/Uz1ED7t3ubdAmSnhwR14VlAahh4fhUywRkdBnwtp3dyiBjUZNqAG0XjTUYzimr9sEQy4xnyIFUupMj-fF7VUq0acWF_fVGmKQdc638oS0I0?purpose=fullsize&v=1\",\"https://images.openai.com/static-rsc-3/_agqiKfcWAt-4et0ZTq-Bk585uDQAAq9ym6mLaYyKgX6t3qfxLG_JCNyJVfQ7B4PK09Yh_FMbYjXxwqEMtlCxIdMUvCp5CQ6Xz-dhewmqtw?purpose=fullsize&v=1\",\"https://images.openai.com/static-rsc-3/wO2tiE9Miex7obC9tcaiiMY7DbCQe9T7HMiFRupFJd_CYU0w-DYCgWVCaFUzWO2YfwN7FSI15pdwB7sL8iJI4v5-rZjJoaqyXlmRmrfgHAM?purpose=fullsize&v=1\",\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/VwC9ctgAfO9eQyvz4nl1SA--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTY0MDtoPTQyNw--/https%3A//media.zenfs.com/en/aol_country_living_372/760b0e56485c3a03fab528185d6b076a\"],\"refs\":[],\"alt\":\"![Image](https://images.openai.com/static-rsc-3/wO2tiE9Miex7obC9tcaiiMY7DbCQe9T7HMiFRupFJd_CYU0w-DYCgWVCaFUzWO2YfwN7FSI15pdwB7sL8iJI4v5-rZjJoaqyXlmRmrfgHAM?purpose=fullsize&v=1)\\n\\n![Image](https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/VwC9ctgAfO9eQyvz4nl1SA--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTY0MDtoPTQyNw--/https%3A//media.zenfs.com/en/aol_country_living_372/760b0e56485c3a03fab528185d6b076a)\\n\\n![Image](https://images.openai.com/static-rsc